<L>__{exterior pointe du lac night}
<A>__{louis running up the steps leading to the gallery. he is crazed with guilt. he looks up and sees }
<B>__{lestat}
<A>__{sitting collected at the head of the steps.}
<B>__{louis}
<A>__{backs away as lestat rises and descends the steps so fluidly he hardly seems to move.}
<C>__{lestat}
<D>__{don't worry. he was white trash, they come at two a penny. i dumped him in the swamp and untied the slave, licked his wounds clean.}
<C>__{louis}
<D>__{you're the devil, aren't you? that's who you are.}
<C>__{lestat}
<P>__{(gently)}
<D>__{i wish i were. but if i were, what would i want with you?}
<C>__{louis}
<D>__{i can't go through with it, i tell you.}
<C>__{lestat}
<D>__{your perfect. your bitter and you're strong.}
<C>__{louis}
<D>__{but why do you want me?}
<C>__{lestat}
<D>__{because you're as strong as i was when i was alive.}
<A>__{louis takes out his flask and drinks. drunkenly, he turns and heads for a nearby swamp.}
